//  EMPIRICAL VERIFICATION (2026-04-05, 605 signature rows, 4 gates)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
//   after L1:   adjusted = 0.6844   margin = +0.0178   grade = weak-breakthrough
//   after L2:   adjusted = 0.7820   margin = +0.1153   grade = strong-breakthrough
//   after L3:   adjusted = 0.8083   margin = +0.1416   grade = strong-breakthrough
//   after L4:   adjusted = 0.8112   margin = +0.1445   grade = strong-breakthrough
//   after L5a:  adjusted = 0.9163   margin = +0.2496   grade = deep-breakthrough
//
//   multi-window (L4):
//     first-half  margin +0.3117  grade = transcendent
//     second-half margin +0.2531  grade = deep-breakthrough
//
//   top coupling pair: finder × telegram  MI = 0.9190  r = +0.618

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  POLICY (what this spec ALLOWS and FORBIDS)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
//   ALLOWED effects: FileIO (read/write), ProcessSensor (ps, sysctl read-only),
//                    Clock
//
//   FORBIDDEN (prime directive):
//     Process killing, throttling (taskpolicy/SIGSTOP/renice),
//     memory purge, compressor tuning, any system write.
//
//   Efficiency gains come from smarter data movement at interface gates,
//   not from controlling processes.

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  12-GATE MATRIX (3 levels × 4 gates)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
//  ┌─────┬───────────────────────┬────────────────────────┬──────────────────────┐
//  │     │  L-PIPELINE           │  L-BREAKTHROUGH        │  L-MK2_HEXA          │
//  │     │  (observation)        │  (validation)          │  (aggregation)       │
//  ├─────┼───────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
//  │ G1  │  SOURCE whitelist     │  paths ≥ 3             │  consensus           │
//  │ G2  │  HASH 60B genome      │  cross-gate > per-gate │  transcendence       │
//  │ G3  │  PHI 6-axis project   │  margin ≥ MARGIN_MIN   │  classify consistency│
//  │ G4  │  INVARIANT rule fire  │  crossed = true        │  verdict aggregate   │
//  └─────┴───────────────────────┴────────────────────────┴──────────────────────┘

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  GENOME SERIALIZATION (60 bytes, little-endian)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
//   Layout: 15 pairs × 4 bytes = 60 bytes total
//   Each pair: f32 little-endian (IEEE 754)
//   Pair ordering: lexicographic on (Axis::ord, Axis::ord)
//     pair 0 = (Cpu, Ram), pair 1 = (Cpu, Gpu), ..., pair 14 = (Power, Io)
//   Hex encoding: 120 hex chars (2 per byte)

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  PROJECTION ANCHORS (non-authoritative)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// Current projection: ~/Dev/air_rs (Rust). Anchors may drift; when
// they do, this spec is correct and the projection must update.
//
//   air_rs/src/gates/mod.rs::classify       → L-PIPELINE.G1
//   air_rs/src/gates/genome.rs::GateGenome  → L-PIPELINE.G2
//   air_rs/src/gates/probes.rs::project     → L-PIPELINE.G3
//   air_rs/src/gates/probes.rs::genome_for  → L-PIPELINE.G4
//   air_rs/src/gates/nexus_merger.rs::*     → L-BREAKTHROUGH.*
//   air_rs/tests/gates_breakthrough.rs      → L-BREAKTHROUGH.G3/G4
//   air_rs/src/bin/airgenome.rs::nexus2_cmd → L-MK2_HEXA.G1/G4
